---
import BlogPost from '../../../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import VideoEmbed from '../../../components/VideoEmbed.astro';
import { getPost, nextPostFor } from '../../../data/posts';

const post = getPost('tipos-de-terapia')!;
const locale = 'en';
---

<BlogPost
  locale={locale}
  title={post.en.title}
  description={post.en.description}
  altPath={`/blog/${locale === "es" ? post.slugEn : post.slugEs}/`}
  category={post.en.category}
  heroImage={post.heroImage}
  heroAlt={post.heroAlt.en}
  heroPosition={post.heroPosition}
  disqusIdentifier={post.en.disqusIdentifier}
  nextPost={nextPostFor(post.id, locale)}
  videos={[
    { name: "What is Somatic Experiencing (SE)?", description: "A trauma-informed therapeutic model that pays attention to the nervous system's responses.", thumbnailUrl: "https://img.youtube.com/vi/2lZfFB-dcbA/hqdefault.jpg", contentUrl: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2lZfFB-dcbA", embedUrl: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/2lZfFB-dcbA" },
    { name: "What is Internal Family Systems (IFS)?", description: "Works with the different parts that coexist within you to integrate conflicting inner voices.", thumbnailUrl: "https://img.youtube.com/vi/DdZZ7sTX840/hqdefault.jpg", contentUrl: "https://youtu.be/DdZZ7sTX840", embedUrl: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/DdZZ7sTX840" },
    { name: "What is Tapping (EFT)?", description: "Combines gentle tapping on specific body points with words to unlock stuck emotions.", thumbnailUrl: "https://img.youtube.com/vi/4ZDjAhuo_6Y/hqdefault.jpg", contentUrl: "https://youtu.be/4ZDjAhuo_6Y", embedUrl: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/4ZDjAhuo_6Y" },
    { name: "What is Core Energetics?", description: "Sees the person as an integration of body, emotions, thoughts and intentions. Works with movement and breathing.", thumbnailUrl: "https://img.youtube.com/vi/WUdo-ENIn7U/hqdefault.jpg", contentUrl: "https://youtube.com/shorts/WUdo-ENIn7U", embedUrl: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/WUdo-ENIn7U" },
  ]}
>
  <p data-reveal style="margin:0 0 52px;">I don't work from a single model because people aren't one-dimensional. Depending on what you bring and how the process unfolds, I integrate these four approaches — always following the rhythm of your experience, not a fixed technique.</p>

  <!-- SE -->
  <div data-reveal style="padding-bottom:48px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--cream);margin-bottom:48px;">
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:20px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:16px;">
      <h2 style="font-family:'Zilla Slab',serif;font-weight:600;color:var(--purple);font-size:clamp(22px,2.5vw,30px);line-height:1.1;margin:0;">Somatic Experiencing <span style="font-size:.65em;font-weight:400;color:var(--sand-d);">(SE)</span></h2>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:clamp(15px,1.1vw,17px);line-height:1.85;color:#3f3a36;margin:0 0 14px;">A trauma-informed therapeutic model. It pays attention to the nervous system's responses to help you regulate what your body holds, respecting the pace your physical experience sets for us.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#6a6460;margin:0 0 20px;">The nervous system has its own intelligence — SE works with that intelligence rather than trying to bypass it. Often the body knows what the mind can't yet put into words.</p>
    <VideoEmbed videoId="2lZfFB-dcbA" title="Watch video: What is Somatic Experiencing (SE)?" />
  </div>

  <!-- IFS -->
  <div data-reveal style="padding-bottom:48px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--cream);margin-bottom:48px;">
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:20px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:16px;">
      <h2 style="font-family:'Zilla Slab',serif;font-weight:600;color:var(--purple);font-size:clamp(22px,2.5vw,30px);line-height:1.1;margin:0;">Internal Family Systems <span style="font-size:.65em;font-weight:400;color:var(--sand-d);">(IFS)</span></h2>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:clamp(15px,1.1vw,17px);line-height:1.85;color:#3f3a36;margin:0 0 14px;">Works with the different "parts" that coexist within you. Helps integrate conflicting inner voices without silencing any of them.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#6a6460;margin:0 0 20px;">We all have a part that wants to move forward and one that holds back. A part that knows what it needs and one that's afraid to ask. IFS creates a space where each can be heard — from the calmest core within you.</p>
    <VideoEmbed videoId="DdZZ7sTX840" title="Watch video: What is Internal Family Systems (IFS)?" />
  </div>

  <!-- EFT -->
  <div data-reveal style="padding-bottom:48px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--cream);margin-bottom:48px;">
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:20px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:16px;">
      <h2 style="font-family:'Zilla Slab',serif;font-weight:600;color:var(--purple);font-size:clamp(22px,2.5vw,30px);line-height:1.1;margin:0;">Tapping <span style="font-size:.65em;font-weight:400;color:var(--sand-d);">(EFT)</span></h2>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:clamp(15px,1.1vw,17px);line-height:1.85;color:#3f3a36;margin:0 0 14px;">Combines gentle tapping on specific body points with words. Useful for unlocking "stuck" emotions. Integrates acupuncture with exposure therapy and neurolinguistic programming.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#6a6460;margin:0 0 20px;">Sometimes there are things we already understand mentally but the body keeps carrying. EFT works directly with that gap — tapping points on the face, chest, and hands while naming what you feel.</p>
    <VideoEmbed videoId="4ZDjAhuo_6Y" title="Watch video: What is Tapping (EFT)?" />
  </div>

  <!-- Core Energetics -->
  <div data-reveal style="padding-bottom:8px;">
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:20px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:16px;">
      <h2 style="font-family:'Zilla Slab',serif;font-weight:600;color:var(--purple);font-size:clamp(22px,2.5vw,30px);line-height:1.1;margin:0;">Core Energetics</h2>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:clamp(15px,1.1vw,17px);line-height:1.85;color:#3f3a36;margin:0 0 14px;">Sees the person as an integration of body, emotions, thoughts, and intentions. Works with movement and breathing to access deep levels. Offers an evolutionary and transpersonal perspective.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#6a6460;margin:0 0 20px;">I'm part of the teaching faculty at Instituto Córpore because this approach helped me understand that sensation, emotion, thought, intention, and action are different facets of the same experience — the wholeness of being human.</p>
    <VideoEmbed videoId="WUdo-ENIn7U" title="Watch video: What is Core Energetics?" />
  </div>
</BlogPost>
